title.narrative: Enhanced support and increased capacities of children, adolescents, and families to protect themselves and to eliminate practices and behaviors harmful to children and adolescents.

description.narrative: In 2019, 9,024 parents and caregivers from two municipalities benefited from parenting education sessions to gain knowledge and skills on caring for and protecting their children, under a partnership between the Ministry of Social Solidarity and Inclusion and UNICEF Timor-Leste. UNICEF also provided technical assistance for the Ministry to deliver its life skills basic education programme, resulting in 120 adolescents increasing their capacities to gain confidence and protect themselves from violence, abuse, neglect and exploitation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:05/02/2020
